definitions.definition: A low-bred , presuming person; a mean , vulgar fellow , especially one that cannot be trusted with a lady.
A person who stands at the door of an omnibus to open and shut it, and to receive fares ; a bus conductor .

main_definition: A low-bred , presuming person; a mean , vulgar fellow , especially one that cannot be trusted with a lady.
secondary_definitions: ( archaic ) A person who stands at the door of an omnibus to open and shut it, and to receive fares ; a bus conductor .
( UK , Ireland , obsolete , slang ) An idle hanger-on about innyards .
